CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 19, 1960, pg. A13 reads: "Brotherhood Festival Participants - Planning on gala tables and exhibits for the March 26 Food Festival at the Hotel Penn Sheraton are, front: Mrs. Amelia Aston, Inter Se Club, and Mrs. Theresa McDaniel, Metoka Club. Standing: Mmes. A. Moncrief, National Achievement Clubs; Earsley Kincaid, T. & C. Artists; Diane Hanna, Greek Room, University of Pittsburgh; Tepla Turner, Daffodil Community Club; Genevieve Medley, Music and Arts Club, and Margaret Fry, O.E.S., Jephtha Chapter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Brotherhood Festival participants, from left, seated: Amelia Aston and Theresa McDaniel; standing: A. Moncrief, Earsley Kincaid, Diane Hanna, Tepla Turner, Genevieve Medley, and Margaret Fry, posed in interior with floral curtains
